buttons.subtitle: Is Olive Oil Healthy
buttons.title: Olive oil health benefits and why you should add it to your diet
buttons.snippet: Olive oil has various health benefits. The majority of the fats in olive oil are made up of monounsaturated fatty acids (MUFAs). These have been shown to increase levels of “good” cholesterol (HDL) while lowering “bad” cholesterol (LDL). Out of all plant-based cooking oils, olive oil has the highest levels of MUFAs.
snippet_highlighted_words: Olive oil has various health benefits

buttons.subtitle: What Kind Of Olive Oil Is Good For You
buttons.title: Extra virgin olive oil or olive oil: Which is healthier? - MedicalNewsToday
buttons.snippet: Extra virgin olive oil is the least processed form of olive oil. Due to this, it retains its natural antioxidants and vitamins, which are often lost during processing. This makes it a more healthful oil than regular olive oil but also makes it a little more expensive.

buttons.subtitle: What Is The Healthiest Olive Oil
buttons.title: 9 healthiest extra virgin olive oils to stock up on - Women's Health
buttons.snippet: 'Olive oil is a staple within the Mediterranean diet, a diet known for its positive effects on many aspects of health. ' 'However, when you dig deeper, it's clear extra virgin olive oil is the healthiest choice as it's made from cold-pressed olives, which means it's less processed than regular olive oil.

buttons.subtitle: Which Olive Oil Is Healthier
buttons.title: What Is Extra Virgin Olive Oil, and Why Is It Healthy? - Healthline
buttons.snippet: Extra virgin olive oil is the least processed variety and is often considered to be the healthiest type of olive oil. It's extracted using natural methods and standardized for purity and certain sensory qualities, such as taste and smell ( 3 ).

buttons.subtitle: Olive Oil For Cooking
buttons.title: Which olive oil is best for cooking and frying? - Treurer
buttons.snippet: Use extra virgin olive oil for cooking, in all its varieties. Properly store olive oil, in a dark and tight environment. Start the process by heating the oil over low heat. Put the food in when it reaches the right temperature for frying.
